This paper deals with best-response mechanisms, which are commonly studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). It also discusses the convergence and incentive compatibility of these mechanisms, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on distributed protocols suggests that it may also be relevant to the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper's investigation of the effects of imperfect strategies on convergence and incentive compatibility could be seen as a form of sensitivity analysis, which is a common topic in the field of simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
